-And everyone speaks and writes in Greek.

29
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:21,680
They also share the same god-

30
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:26,320
-And every four years, Olympic games are held to honor them.

31
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:30,320
Religion was polytheistic, with many gods.

32
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:37,240
They had different special functions and work areas, you might say.

33
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:43,360
This is this gang: Zeus, Athena, Poseidon, Apollon, Aphrodite, etc.

34
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:49,880
Although much holds the city states together, much else separates them.

35
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:54,400
They have their own laws and political systems.

36
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:58,560
In addition, they are constantly at war with each other.

37
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:03,720
Two arch enemies are the leading city states Athens and Sparta.

38
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:07,520
We take a closer look at them.
 First Athens.

39
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:12,520
Athens has its heyday during the 400s before our time-

40
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:16,000
-And here the idea of democracy is born.

41
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:20,760
It is a long political process where one is trying to find medium-

42
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:27,960
-Ee to take power from the rich aristocratic family heads-

43
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:31,800
-and distribute it to more.

44
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:36,040
This is solved by giving all citizens voting rights.

45
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:41,920
The parenthesis is that only free, Athenian men are counted as citizens.

46
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:46,440
In Athens, women, foreigners and slaves also lived.

47
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:52,400
They had no right of voting or the right to speak in this system.

48
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:59,760
It is a democratic principle, but not a democracy like today.

49
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:05,840
Elections were not seen as a democratic institution, because they could be influenced.

50
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:10,320
The lot was the democratic way to choose people.

51
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:14,120
With it comes rights and obligations.

52
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:18,320
If you are drawn forward, you are obliged to take your responsibility.

53
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:24,040
If you are drawn into the council, you need to be able to convince the free Athenian men.

54
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:29,400
You both need good ideas and be a skilled speaker.

55
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:34,040
Many philosophers were also a teacher of rhetoric.

56
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:37,600
There is a small bonus in the system.

57
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:43,800
A politician you dislike can get a land -defeated with 6,000 votes.

58
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:48,040
It is seen as a protection for democracy.

59
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:54,720
While Athens focuses on democracy, life in Sparta looks different.

60
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:58,600
It is one of the few monarchies in Greece-

61
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:03,320
-But above all the view of society and the war distinguishes them.

62
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:06,000
The collective went before-

63
