-And the whole community was organized according to the best of the state.

64
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:15,600
Citizens were some kind of warrior.

65
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:21,240
War characterizes the entire life of the Spartans, and they conquer land.

66
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:28,200
You should always be ready for battle, and loss is nothing that is accepted.

67
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:35,840
Boys are raised by the state and do military service until they are thirty.

68
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:41,000
For people in Sparta, the state and the collective are at the center.

69
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:44,960
One should live a sparse life.

70
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:47,880
One would live spartan.

71
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:53,720
You looked down at material wealth, so you would live poor.

72
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:59,960
The city states differ, but nothing unites as an external enemy.

73
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:06,280
One of these has the city states in the east: the Persian Empire.

74
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:12,040
The Persians are an arch enemy of the Greek world.

75
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:16,520
Athens and Sparta are side by side against the Persians in several wars.

76
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:23,320
At Thermopyle, Greece goes on a loss, and you dream of revenge.

77
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:29,720
When Alexander the Great inherits power in the Greek Kingdom of Macedonia-

78
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:32,200
-he thinks revenge.

79
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:38,520
He leaves on an expedition east and is successful.

80
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:42,000
He conquers the entire Persian kingdom.

81
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:47,480
Finally he reigns over today's Greece, Turkey-

82
