A man should be strong and have control.

106
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:40,680
One had control over one's body, their feelings and lustar-

107
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:43,280
-And even over others.

108
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:49,160
After all, they controlled your wife, their children and their slaves.

109
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:54,840
The woman should be everything the man is not: passive and without control.

110
00:08:55,000 --> 00:09:00,920
A slave has no norms or ideals, because it is not seen as a human being.

111
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:07,720
This is included in part two - the Roman antiquity.

112
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:12,040
For a long time, the Greek and Roman antiquity coexist.

113
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:18,440
From the beginning, Rome is a city state, but here you have other ambitions.

114
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:23,640
This with independent city states is nothing to the Romans.

115
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:27,920
They will build an empire with Rome in the center.

116
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:35,520
Rome puts areas underneath, and after three wars they conquer Carthage.

117
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:42,840
You are at the center of the Mediterranean world and an established superpower.

118
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:46,240
Now nothing can stop the Romans.

119
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:50,080
The Mediterranean starts to be called "Our Sea"-

120
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:54,800
-And you control areas up to today's United Kingdom.

121
00:09:54,960 --> 00:10:00,120
In addition to the Greek areas, they also take their gods.

122
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:05,960
They get new, Roman names.
 Hello then, Zeus.
 Welcome, Jupiter.

123
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:10,920
But for the people in conquered areas - what happens to them?

124
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:16,200
How does the life change to belong to the Roman Empire?

125
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:22,800
A principle is that Rome does not interfere in local affairs-

126
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,560
-or the religious life.

127
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:29,800
You let people speak the language they speak.

128
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:33,760
In the eastern part you still speak Greek.

129
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:40,280
You are relatively open and take in citizens from parts of the Roman Empire.

130
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:44,920
In the end, all men can become citizens.

131
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:50,120
Some may get full citizenship and others without voting rights.

132
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:54,160
The Romans call their politics to disintegrate and rule.

133
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:57,680
Different conditions to different areas-

134
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:02,120
-makes it harder for them to come together against Rome.

135
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:07,680
Those who are given voting rights must go the long way to Rome.

136
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:10,920
This is where the Republic is governed.

137
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:17,840
Here is the Senate, an advisory body with the wealthiest men of the kingdom.

138
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:22,480
The officials ensure that the decisions are enforced.

139
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:25,880
They are selected two and two for one year at the time-

140
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:30,240
-To avoid getting too much power.

141
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:35,760
The two most important officials - the consuls - lead the kingdom in war.

142
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:38,440
Then there are people's congregations.

143
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:44,200
In those who appoint officials, all male citizens are allowed to vote.

144
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:47,840
In the Republic of Rome, big cities grow in

145
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:53,160
-But wherever you live, it gets carbon black as soon as the sun goes down.

146
00:11:53,320 --> 00:12:00,040
Here is a Roman oil lamp - the only light you have except the sun.

147
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:07,440
You must have many, and it was one of the most common objects.

148
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:13,320
They are manufactured on running bands in workshops around the kingdom.

149
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:17,800
The workshops were named after the owner.

150
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:23,840
The names were printed on the bottom, so you knew where the lamp came from.

151
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:28,360
It was one of the first objects that were mass -produced.

152
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:33,360
It is also true that these brands are pirated.

153
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:39,920
Much of the workforce is slaves, and most are conquered on the battlefields.

154
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:43,600
Something the Romans may be that war-

155
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:49,320
-And here is one of the foremost generals: Julius Caesar.

156
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:55,640
He dreams of more power and a greater role than is allowed in the system.

157
00:12:55,800 --> 00:13:01,360
Caesar is chosen as a consul, but you cannot be re -elected.

158
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:05,840
His position is not quite in the system.

159
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:09,720
How does he solve it?
 By force.

160
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:14,920
He trains towards Rome, and that leads to power struggle and civil war.

161
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:19,960
In the end, Caesar stands in the capital with the sign "Veni, Vidi, Vici".

162
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:25,160
"I came I saw I conquered."
 Caesar is proclaimed dictator.

163
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:29,480
First in one year, then ten and finally life.

164
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:32,600
Now "dictator" gets a negative tone.

165
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:37,840
It would have been something you could be chosen in a crisis situation.

166
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:42,280
If both the consuls fall, someone must control Rome.

167
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:48,760
Then you can choose a dictator of a maximum of six months, but not for a lifetime.

168
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:55,680
Therefore, Caesar becomes less popular and ultimately murdered by senators.

169
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:59,000
Then the empire takes over.

170
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:03,280
Rome is governed by an emperor, and everyone gets the title Augustus.

171
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:07,800
Now follows a period of 200 years of peace.

172
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:14,280
Much we recognize now is established: monuments, bridges and aqueducts.

173
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:20,320
For the Romans, life is quite comfortable, but all good has an end.

174
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:26,440
It crackles in the joints, and the Roman Empire is in crisis.

175
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:32,120
The Conquest War has subsided, and they gave all the slaves.

176
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:38,920
The governing bodies are forced to raise the tax, which deteriorates for farmers.

177
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:42,520
A new religion emerges: Christianity.

178
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:45,640
Christians refuse to worship the gods of Rome

179
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:50,440
-The Christianity is banned and the Christians are persecuted.

180
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:54,400
But with Emperor Constantine, everything changes.

181
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:59,640
Constantine perhaps expects the potential of Christianity

182
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:05,440
-Som something that can hold together the now rather fragmentary empire.

183
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:09,840
By the end of the 300s, other religious expressions are banned

184
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,920
-and Christianity is state religion.

185
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:20,560
Now everyone is forced to release the Roman gods and worship the Christian.

186
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:26,600
Konstantin prohibits crucifixion, the Peter's Church funds in Rom-

187
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:30,000
-And makes Sunday work -free.

188
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:33,960
But not even that can hold the kingdom together.

189
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:39,840
Power moved to Constantinople - today's ottanbul-

190
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:46,400
-And that city is getting bigger and more powerful than Rome.

191
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:51,360
The Great Empire is split into two: Västrom and Östrom.

192
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:56,680
Östrom grows strongly and later becomes the Byzantine Empire-

193
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:59,280
-As lives on for a thousand years.

194
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:05,560
For Västrom things go worse, and the last emperor loses power.

195
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:11,760
It is said that antiquity ends in 476, when the last emperor is set aside.

196
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:14,040
We have found that.

197
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:19,000
The question is whether anyone who lived in 476 noticed any difference 477.

198
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:22,160
That an era was over - probably not.

199
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:25,400
There was probably no giant difference-

200
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:32,360
-But antiquity has been symbolized a wonderful time with philosophy and knowledge.

201
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:35,000
We have read the philosophers.

202
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:40,280
They do not tell how they exploit women and slave-

203
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:43,120
-and how others are treated.

204
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:50,720
We only got this ideal image from those who were doing well.

205
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:55,600
The second picture we have had to dig out.

206
00:16:55,760 --> 00:17:01,560
The democratic heritage has been given a great place, and it has often been idealized.

207
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:07,040
Not least Greek democracy, but it wasn't always.

208
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:11,840
Only in the 1850s began the ancient democracy-

209
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:15,280
-Ses as a political role model.

210
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:21,360
Before that, democracy was regarded as a mob.

211
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:26,200
The idea of a Roman Empire power has inspired rulers.

212
00:17:26,360 --> 00:17:33,080
Napoleon, Mussolini and Hitler used Roman symbols.

213
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:39,560
From the first democratic steps in Greece to the military empire in Rome.

214
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:45,720
In ancient times, different types of rule and view of power may take place.

215
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:52,560
Whatever you want to legitimize, you can often find it in antiquity.

